The paper focuses on accelerating the training of CNN models, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed solution involves restructuring batch normalization layers, which is a specific technique used in deep learning (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of memory-access reduction techniques, which is related to computer architecture (cs.DC).
